INSERT OR REPLACE INTO intelligence_shards (id, name, sector, content) VALUES ('SUPERPOWERS/research/grok_validation_2026-05-01/logs/LOG_cluster-enhancement.md', 'LOG_cluster-enhancement.md', 'SUPERPOWERS/RESEARCH/GROK_VALIDATION_2026-05-01/LOGS', '# Log: cluster-enhancement.pdf

[VERIFIED_URLS]
1. https://github.com/lawrencewzen/hero-coding
2. https://github.com/robbyczgw-cla/hermes-web-search-plus
3. https://github.com/OpenInterpretability/mechreward
4. https://github.com/OpenInterpretability/notebooks
5. https://github.com/OpenInterpretability/cli
6. https://arxiv.org/abs/2504.12345

[GROK_CLAIM_VS_REALITY]
- **hero-coding**: Grok claims it provides harness patterns that strengthen Oz-style workflow. Reality: It is a stateless coding agent MVP relying on OpenAI-compatible APIs. It can be run locally if pointed to local inference nodes, but natively expects API keys.
- **hermes-web-search-plus**: Grok claims local SearXNG support enables fully sovereign web search. Reality: It heavily integrates with cloud search providers (Serper, Tavily, Exa, Firecrawl). Cloud leak risk is high unless strictly configured for SearXNG.
- **mechreward**: Grok claims it''s a direct upgrade for GEPA v2 (mechanistic features as evolution rewards). Reality: It has strong dependencies on Hugging Face (TRL, SAELens), which violates strict offline/zero-trust sovereignty unless models/data are fully air-gapped.
- **Zero-Trust / SPIFFE / mTLS**: None of the audited repositories explicitly implement SPIFFE/SPIRE or mTLS for service identity. They rely on standard API keys or local filesystem state.

[SOVEREIGNTY_SCORE] 
5/10 - High risk of cloud dependency leaks (Hugging Face, external search APIs, OpenAI-compatible endpoints) and lack of robust zero-trust infrastructure (no SPIFFE/mTLS).

[COUNTER_RESEARCH_NOTES]
- **Node D Feasibility**: Running these tools on Node D (Zero-Trust/Offline) will require significant modifications. API calls must be intercepted and routed to Node C/Node B local inference.
- The `mechreward` library needs to be scrubbed of Hugging Face telemetry and hardcoded cloud endpoints.
- `hermes-web-search-plus` must be hard-locked to local SearXNG to prevent external network egress.
');
