## 🏗️ 1. ARCHITECTURAL SYMMETRY
The **Pretext HUD v2** is a monolithic, high-performance UI architecture that achieves bit-identical design parity across Web (Next.js) and Mobile (Flutter).

- **Core Engine:** Pretext (Low-level rendering of Paragraph APIs).
- **Aesthetic:** Frosted Gruvbox (Phase 92 Baseline).
- **Hardening:** Circular Context Rings (Node A/B/C pressure signals).

---

## ⚡ 2. MATERIALIZED COMPONENTS

### 2.1 PretextShroud.tsx (Web)
The single-file UI baseline for the desktop dashboard. Features `react-grid-layout` integration and Three.js 3D Neural Promenade overlays.

### 2.2 PretextScreen.dart (Mobile)
The native Android entry point. Replaces high-level Flutter widgets with `PretextPainter` for high-density documentation and terminal-stream rendering.

---

## 🕹️ 3. CAPABILITIES
- **Linguistic Folding:** Agents can fold/unfold complex thought-trees in the HUD.
- **Resonance Pulses:** Visual hardening indicators when logic is verified by Vesper.
- **Swipe-to-Fork:** Mobile-exclusive interaction for branching reasoning paths (Phase 92.4).

---
