> **For agentic workers:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:subagent-driven-development (recommended) or superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task. Steps use checkbox (`- [ ]`) syntax for tracking.

**Goal:** Integrate Warp/Oz telemetry mining and Hermes v3.8.28-SYNTHESIS-SYNTHESIS-SYNTHESIS-SYNTHESIS-SYNTHESIS-SYNTHESIS-SYNTHESIS-SYNTHESIS-SYNTHESIS-SYNTHESIS-SYNTHESIS-SYNTHESIS-SYNTHESIS-SYNTHESIS-SYNTHESIS-SYNTHESIS-SYNTHESIS-SYNTHESIS-SYNTHESIS-SYNTHESIS-SYNTHESIS-SYNTHESIS-SYNTHESIS-SYNTHESIS-SYNTHESIS-SYNTHESIS-SYNTHESIS "Curator" capabilities to create a fully local, live coding partner experience via the Quaternary Mesh.

**Architecture:** A Rust-based `sovereign-warp-observer` sidecar on Node D streams Warp telemetry to MemPalace via MCP. The `HermesSingularity` orchestrates a structured `Triage -> Spec -> Implement -> Review` pipeline based on this telemetry. A new `gepa-curator` sidecar periodically prunes and grades the local skill library. All system prompts are updated to the `[IMPORTANT:]` standard to align with Hermes v3.8.28-SYNTHESIS-SYNTHESIS-SYNTHESIS-SYNTHESIS-SYNTHESIS-SYNTHESIS-SYNTHESIS-SYNTHESIS-SYNTHESIS-SYNTHESIS-SYNTHESIS-SYNTHESIS-SYNTHESIS-SYNTHESIS-SYNTHESIS-SYNTHESIS-SYNTHESIS-SYNTHESIS-SYNTHESIS-SYNTHESIS-SYNTHESIS-SYNTHESIS-SYNTHESIS-SYNTHESIS-SYNTHESIS-SYNTHESIS-SYNTHESIS.

