This document defines every command available to the operator via the **Crush CLI**, **Hermes Ink**, and the **Quaternary Mesh** arteries.

---

## 🏗️ 1. SYSTEM IGNITION & ARTERY PATH
Commands for starting hardware nodes and establishing the cognitive artery.

| Command | Context | Description |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| `crush start` | **CLI** | Ignites the full system in headless mode. |
| `crush start --lite` | **CLI** | Starts the lightweight Artery mode (Node A only). |
| `crush start --interactive` | **CLI** | Starts with the TUI dashboard enabled. |
| `crush proxy` | **CLI** | Starts the high-throughput VSB/Mmap physical proxy. |
| `crush shut-down` | **CLI** | **DANGER:** Purges all local Machina processes immediately. |
| `crush reconstruct` | **CLI** | Cleans and rebuilds the Sovereign Vault and memory core. |
| `crush profile [name]` | **CLI** | Performs an atomic identity shift (e.g., SOVEREIGN_OS -> RESEARCHER). |
| `ignite-all.sh` | **Shell** | Sequential ignition of Nodes A, B, C, and D. |

## 🛡️ 2. AUTHORITY & GOVERNANCE
Commands for managing zero-trust boundaries and sovereign permissions.

| Command | Context | Description |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| `crush sovereign-mode on` | **CLI** | Bypasses the Rules Strategic Oracle for emergency unconstrained logic. |
| `crush radar --public on` | **CLI** | Sets the tactical radar to public broadcast (VSB UDP). |
| `crush vault [seal/open]` | **CLI** | Secures or unseals steganographic archives using SOVEREIGN_KEY. |
| `crush chaos network` | **CLI** | Simulates network latency/failure for mesh resilience testing. |
| `/veto [proposal_id]` | **Hermes** | Force-rejects an agent''s proposed implementation trajectory. |
| `/pass [proposal_id]` | **Hermes** | Manual override to approve an agent trajectory. |

## ⌨️ 3. AGENTIC REASONING (Hermes Ink)
High-fidelity commands available inside the Hermes reasoning shell.

| Command | Purpose | Description |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| `/research [topic]` | **Research** | Dispatches a Node D swarm for deep topic analysis. |
| `/forge [item_type]` | **Synthesis** | Materializes a new simulation or OS asset via Skill-Factory. |
| `/datalog [query]` | **Synapse** | Executes a raw DataScript/Datalog query against os_triplets. |
| `/spatial [action]` | **Spatial** | Interacts with the 3D Neural Promenade (e.g., /spatial latch). |
| `/propose [intent]` | **Goal** | Submits a strategic proposal for user/strategist review. |
| `/sync` | **Scribe** | Triggers bit-identical synchronization of all manifests. |

## 🛠️ 4. TACTICAL & DEVELOPMENT
Commands for real-time interaction and system maintenance.

| Command | Target | Description |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| `crush hack [action]` | **Director** | Sends a tactical intent (shut-down, switch-profile). |
| `crush scan [type]` | **Director** | Scans environment for objectives, hazards, or cover. |
| `crush crop-scan [x y]` | **Director** | High-fidelity vision capture of specific host-screen coordinates. |
| `crush belt list` | **Registry** | Lists active/available hardware sidecars and VRAM usage. |
| `crush social [args]` | **Social** | Manages federated agent reputation and social shards. |
| `crush logseq [cmd]` | **Mesh** | Atomic block manipulation for the Logseq host app. |
| `crush dev [cmd]` | **Internal** | Manual state forcing (deadlock, dream, mmap-write). |
| `crush meeting [id]` | **Hall** | Forces a Sovereign Hall meeting for specific trace resolution. |
| `crush thought-stream` | **Pipe** | Raw tail of the Node B reasoning artery. |
| `npm run scribe` | **Manifests** | Synchronizes versioning across all documentation. |
| `npm run reckoning` | **Validation** | Executes the 100% mesh integrity validation suite. |

